00357 class SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES
00358 {
00359   public:
00360     friend class SecurityHelper;    
00362     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() 
00363     {
00364         nSrtpKeyLength = 0 ;
00365         nSmimeKeyLength = 0 ;
00366         nSrtpLevel = SRTP_LEVEL_NONE ;
00367         memset(szSrtpKey, 0, sizeof(szSrtpKey));
00368         memset(szSmimeKeyDer, 0, sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer));
00369         memset(dbLocation, 0, sizeof(dbLocation));
00370         memset(szMyCertNickname, 0, sizeof(szMyCertNickname));
00371         memset(szCertDbPassword, 0, sizeof(szCertDbPassword));
00372     }    
00374     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00375     {
00376         copyData(ref);
00377     }    
00379     virtual ~SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() { }    
00381     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& operator=(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00382     {
00383         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00384         copyData(ref);
00385         return *this;
00386     }    
00391     void setSrtpKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00392     {
00393         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey);
00394         memcpy(szSrtpKey, szKey, safeLen);
00395         nSrtpKeyLength = safeLen;
00396     }    
00401     void setSmimeKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00402     {
00403         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer);
00404         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, szKey, safeLen);
00405         nSmimeKeyLength = safeLen;
00406     }
00410     void setSecurityLevel(SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL security) { nSrtpLevel = security; }
00414     const char* getSrtpKey() const  { return szSrtpKey; }    
00419     const char* getSmimeKey() const { return szSmimeKeyDer; }
00423     const int getSrtpKeyLength() const  { return nSrtpKeyLength; }
00428     const int getSmimeKeyLength() const { return nSmimeKeyLength; }
00432     const int getSecurityLevel() const {return nSrtpLevel;}
00438     const char* getCertDbLocation() const { return dbLocation; }
00439   private:
00440     SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL nSrtpLevel;
00441     char szSrtpKey[MAX_SRTP_KEY_LENGTH];
00442     int  nSrtpKeyLength;    
00443     char szSmimeKeyDer[MAX_SMIME_KEY_LENGTH];
00444     int  nSmimeKeyLength; 
00445     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00446     char dbLocation[256];                         
00447     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00448     char szMyCertNickname[32];   
00449     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00450     char szCertDbPassword[MAX_PASSWORD_LENGTH];   
00451     void copyData(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00452     {
00453         nSrtpLevel = ref.nSrtpLevel;
00454         nSrtpKeyLength = ref.nSrtpKeyLength;
00455         nSmimeKeyLength = ref.nSmimeKeyLength;
00456         memcpy(szSrtpKey, ref.szSrtpKey, ref.nSrtpKeyLength);
00457         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, ref.szSmimeKeyDer, ref.nSmimeKeyLength);
00458         strncpy(dbLocation, ref.dbLocation, sizeof(dbLocation) - 1);
00459         strncpy(szMyCertNickname, ref.szMyCertNickname, sizeof(szMyCertNickname) - 1);
00460         strncpy(szCertDbPassword, ref.szCertDbPassword, sizeof(szCertDbPassword) - 1);
00461     }
00462 };

00511 struct SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY
00512 {
00514     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY()
00515     {
00516         cbSize = sizeof(SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY);
00517         type = SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE_TYPE;
00518         handle = NULL;
00519     }
00521     ~SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY()
00522     {
00523         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00524         {
00525 #ifdef      _WIN32
00526             if (handle) ((IUnknown*)handle)->Release();
00527 #endif              
00528         }
00529     }
00530     
00532     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00533     {
00534         copy(ref);
00535     }
00537     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& operator=(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00538     {
00539         // check for assignment to self
00540         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00541         copy(ref);
00542         return *this;
00543     }    
00544         
00545     int cbSize;                     
00546     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY_TYPE type;   
00547     union
00548     {
00549         SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE handle;  
00550         IBaseFilter* filter;        
00551     };
00552 private:
00553     void copy(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00554     {
00555         cbSize = ref.cbSize;
00556         type = ref.type;
00557         handle = ref.handle;
00558         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00559         {
00560 #ifdef      _WIN32
00561             // we should addRef here.
00562             if (handle) ((IBaseFilter*)handle)->AddRef();
00563 #endif            
00564         }
00565     }
00566     
00567 };

00581 struct SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS

00586         memset((void*)cInterface, 0, sizeof(cInterface));
00587         memset((void*)cIpAddress, 0, sizeof(cIpAddress));
00588         eContactType = CONTACT_AUTO;
00589         eTransportType = TRANSPORT_UDP ;
00590         id = 0;
00591         iPort = -1;
00592     }
00594     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00595     {
00596         strcpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface);
00597         strcpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress);
00598         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00599         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00600         id = ref.id;
00601         iPort = ref.iPort;
00602     }
00604     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& operator=(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00605     {
00606         // check for assignment to self
00607         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00608         strcpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface);
00609         strcpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress);
00610         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00611         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00612         id = ref.id;
00613         iPort = ref.iPort;
00614         return *this;
00615     }    
00616     SIPX_CONTACT_ID     id;              
00617     SIPX_CONTACT_TYPE   eContactType ;   
00618     SIPX_TRANSPORT_TYPE eTransportType ; 
00619     char                cInterface[32] ; 
00620     char                cIpAddress[32] ; 
00621     int                 iPort ;          
00622 };
